# lm(y~???x,data)
attach(ad)
mod1 <- lm(Sales ~ TV)
#head(predict(mod1))
ggplot(ad, aes(x=TV, y=Sales))+
  geom_point(alpha=0.6, col="coral")+
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE)+
  geom_segment(aes(xend = TV, yend = predict(mod1)),alpha=0.2)

Additive Assumption

# In this situation, given a fixed budget of $100,000, spending half on radio and
# half on TV may increase sales more than allocating the entire amount to either
# TV or to radio. In marketing, this is known as a synergy effect, and in
# statistics it is referred to as an interaction effect

modinter<-lm(Sales~TV+Radio+TV*Radio, data=ad)
summary(modinter)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = Sales ~ TV + Radio + TV * Radio, data = ad)
## 
## Residuals:
